2? \n                        c = ..............\n\n2) In respect to the values of the variables a, b and c that \"close\" the shape2, try to express the area of each shape as a product of the variable c.\n  (use the variables a, b and c instead of numbers):\n\n         Area.shape1 = c*...\n         Area.shape2 = c*...\n\n     What is the relation between the area of these two shapes?\n\n3) In respect to the values of the variables a, b and c that \"close\" the shape2, try to express the area of the shape2 by using only squares.\n\n         Area.shape2 = \n\n4) Combine the answers at 1), 2) and 3) in order to form an identity. \nThen try to prove it algebraically. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  TIP\n------------------\nWhen the shape2 is \"closed\", then the two shapes have the same perimeter and the same area. \n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}